; galaxigans_saucers.was — PRIME SAUCER boss-flyby aliens (levels 1-3).
; Big horizontal capital-ship aliens that slowly cross the TOP of the screen as a
; bonus/menace flyby (Galaga bonus-saucer idea, scaled up). Each is a 32x16 indexed
; hex bitmap (EVERY "row" is EXACTLY 32 chars; rows pack contiguously) with a 2-frame
; animation so it shimmers as it drifts. Each has its own 16-colour shaded palette.
;
; SPRITE CONVENTION: each char is a palette index '0'-'9' -> 0-9, 'A'-'F' -> 10-15,
; '.' -> 0 = TRANSPARENT. Index 0 transparent, index 1 = dark outline.
;
; =====================================================================================
; INTENDED BEHAVIOUR (I'll wire SprAddFrame / SprSetPalette + movement)
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
;   - The prime saucer is a single off-formation craft, NOT part of the 8x5 grid.
;   - It enters fully OFF-SCREEN on one side, drifts SLOWLY straight across the TOP
;     band of the play-field, then exits the far side and despawns.
;   - Drift band  : y = 24  (above the formation, which starts at GRID_Y0 = 56).
;   - Direction   : alternate each spawn (L->R, then R->L, ...). Start x = -32 going
;     right (vx = +PRIME_VX) or x = FIELD_W (640) going left (vx = -PRIME_VX).
;   - Speed (slow, menacing — slower than a diver's 3 px/frame):
;       Level 1 SCOUT       PRIME_VX = 2   (fast-LOOKING but still a slow crawl)
;       Level 2 CRUISER     PRIME_VX = 1   (heavier)
;       Level 3 DREADNOUGHT PRIME_VX = 1   (slowest / heaviest; ~every 2nd frame ok too)
;   - Animation   : flip frame0/frame1 every ~10 frames (6 Hz shimmer) — running lights
;     cycle, engine glow pulses, dish/eye rotates. Independent of x-movement.
;   - Bonus       : if a player bullet hits it, it dies in a flash and awards bonus pts:
;       Level 1 = 300, Level 2 = 600, Level 3 = 1000 (scale as you like). It does NOT
;     drop bombs and does NOT collide-kill the player (pure bonus menace).
;   - Spawn timing (per level — a flyby is an occasional event, not constant):
;       Level 1 : first at ~6 s, then every ~14 s while the wave is alive.
;       Level 2 : first at ~5 s, then every ~12 s.
;       Level 3 : first at ~4 s, then every ~10 s (dread shows up sooner / more often).
;     (Frames @60fps: L1 360/840, L2 300/720, L3 240/600.) Only one prime alive at once.
; =====================================================================================

module Galaxigans

.balign 16
.DATA
.balign 16

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; SAUCER 1 — "VESPER SCOUT"  (LEVEL 1) : sleek, fast-looking recon dart.
;   A narrow swept hull with a glowing forward sensor eye and a twin ion trail. Frame
;   anim = the two running-light strakes + the tail flame cycle (dart looks like it's
;   streaking). Palette (slot, index -> 0x00RRGGBB):
;     0 transparent
;     1 0x00081018  dark outline / shadow
;     2 0x00123A52  hull shadow (teal-steel)
;     3 0x001E5E80  hull mid
;     4 0x002E86AE  hull light
;     5 0x0055B8D6  hull highlight (cyan edge)
;     6 0x0000E0FF  running light A (bright cyan) — lit in frame0
;     7 0x00007088  running light A dim — shown in frame1
;     8 0x00FFE14A  sensor eye core (amber)
;     9 0x00FF7A1E  sensor eye ring / ion flame mid (orange)
;     A 0x00FFD080  ion flame hot tip (pale gold)
;     B 0x00B02050  flame tail dim (deep rose) — engine-pulse low
;     C 0x00FFFFFF  spark highlight
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.balign 16
; frame 0 — running lights LIT (6), flame long/hot. Nose at RIGHT, ion trail at LEFT.
saucer1Art   BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "...............234432..........."
             BYTE "BA9..........234566654322......."
             BYTE ".BA9.......2345666CC66543222...."
             BYTE "..BA9....2345668888866654322...."
             BYTE "AAAA9...23456889888866654322...."
             BYTE "..BA9....2345668888866654322...."
             BYTE ".BA9.......2345666CC66543222...."
             BYTE "BA9..........234566654322......."
             BYTE "...............234432..........."
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
; frame 1 — running lights DIM (7), flame short/pulsed (B/rose), sensor flicker.
saucer1Art2  BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "...............234432..........."
             BYTE ".B9..........234577754322......."
             BYTE "..B9.......2345777CC77543222...."
             BYTE "...B9....2345778888877754322...."
             BYTE "BBBB9...23457789888877754322...."
             BYTE "...B9....2345778888877754322...."
             BYTE "..B9.......2345777CC77543222...."
             BYTE ".B9..........234577754322......."
             BYTE "...............234432..........."
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"
             BYTE "................................"

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; SAUCER 2 — "MAROON CRUISER"  (LEVEL 2) : bigger armoured disc-cruiser.
;   A broad lenticular saucer hull with a rotating central dome/dish, three running
;   lights along each rim and twin under-slung pods. Frame anim = the dome spin (the
;   bright quadrant of the dish jumps) + rim lights chase. Palette:
;     0 transparent
;     1 0x00100408  dark outline
;     2 0x00401018  hull shadow (oxblood)
;     3 0x00702028  hull mid-dark
;     4 0x009A3038  hull mid (crimson)
;     5 0x00C85048  hull light
;     6 0x00E88060  hull highlight (warm copper)
;     7 0x00FFC890  rim bevel / metal sheen
;     8 0x002A2238  dome shadow (violet-steel)
;     9 0x006A4FA8  dome mid (amethyst)
;     A 0x00B08CF0  dome light
;     B 0x00E6D2FF  dome glint (rotating highlight)
;     C 0x0030FF9A  rim running light (toxic green) — chase
;     D 0x00126040  rim light dim
;     E 0x00FFE45A  pod thruster glow (amber)
